<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658540>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGS. 14–23. Photomicrographs of Hartmannula derouxi nov. spec. from life (14–17), after protargol (18–20) and silver nitrate impregnation (21–23). (14) Ventral view, arrowheads indicate contractile vacuoles in anterior portion. (15) Dorsal view, showing the gel-like layer on the cell surface (arrow), macronucleus (arrowhead) and arched recess (double-arrowheads). (16) Ventral view, focusing on cytostome (arrow) and several contractile vacuoles in posterior portion (arrowheads). (17) Showing the podite (arrow). (18) Ventral view of infraciliature. (19) Infraciliature of anterior portion, note the preoral kinety (arrow), cytostome (double-arrowheads) and macronucleus (arrowhead). (20) Showing the terminal fragment (arrowheads). (21) Focusing on contractile vacuole pores on the right of ventral surface (arrows). (22) Ventral view, arrows indicate the contractile vacuole pores on the left of ventral surface. (23) Silverline system on dorsal side. Bars: 50 µm (14–17); 40 µm (18); 20 µm (19–22); 10 µm (23)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4658540/files/figure.png" .

