<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658536>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGS. 1–9. Morphology and infraciliature of Hartmannula derouxi nov. spec. from life (1–3, 6), after protargol (4, 7, 8) and silver nitrate impregnation (5, 9). (1) Ventral view of a typical individual, arrow indicates gel-like substance. (2) Dorsal and lateral views of a well-fed specimen. (3) Dorsal and lateral view of a small individual. (4) Infraciliature, showing equatorial fragment (arrowhead), macronucleus (double-arrowheads) and podite (arrow). (5) Ventral view, showing the arrangement of contractile vacuole pores. (6) Dorsal view. (7) Infraciliature of oral field; (8) Dorsal view of anterior portion, arrow marks terminal fragment. (9) Silverline system on dorsal side. Co, circumoral kineties; CVP, contractile vacuole pores; FvK, frontoventral kineties; LK, left kineties; Pr, preoral kinety; RK, right kineties; SoK, suboral kineties. Bars: 40µm (1, 4, 7, 9); 60 µm (2, 3)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4658536/files/figure.png" .

